deck: Free comic teaching children to 'duck and cover'
description:
During the cold war Americans were afraid of an atom-bomb attack by the Russians. The American government spent a lot of money teaching people to 'duck and cover'. The Civil Defence made comics, movies and thought children at schools all over the nation to be prepared for when the bombs came by taking shelter.

The comic went through six printings during the 50's and early 60's.

Lloyd believes as much as a boy ever has. As such, he's ready to be heartbroken. In the sixth of seven stories set around a single club night, we join the fledgling phonomancer, as he sifts through the evening's wreckage and tries to piece together meaning with glue,scissors, and magic. Complete with two back-up stories with art from PJ HOLDEN (2000AD, FEARLESS) and ADAM CADWELL (The Everyday).
name: Ready to Be Heartbroken; Your Song; Atlantis to Interzone

description:
Enter and abandon all hope in the most terrifying Realm in the world. This is a tale no mortal can witness without gibbering into madness!

Each year, on October 31st, the nefarious spirits of Pirates and Ninjas rise from their graves to wage their eternal war. Each side seeks to woo a living maiden and take her back to Hell to rule as Queen of the Undead. Dead Pirate Captain Mad "Jolly" McMadman and his crew clash with the dreaded Ninja Clan of the Thousand Cuts, led by Naga the Snake, the deadliest Dead Ninja alive! Witness as they vie (and murder) for the attentions of the fair Druscilla, the Waif Princess da Vinci. From midnight to midnight on the Day of Blood, no other mortal they encounter can be allowed to live! When Ghost Pirates and Ninjas come a-callin', lock up your daughters and throw away the keys!

description: The king of the vampires is back. As if the hoards of demons that Pete Wisdom let out in order to defeat the Skrulls in England werenâ€™t enough, now DRACULA has entered the scene. What does he want with Spitfire? And how will an election help his cause? You better hope that Captain Britain and the rest of MI13 have a way to defeat him! Plus: Meggan is Captain Britain's wife, an X-Man in Hell. And she's going to fight her way home. Over years, bargains, battles, with only her love to guide her. name: To Challenge A Champion!

description: Sakura aids Rainbow Mika in her rematch against Zangief as Dan continues to seek out the young Street Fighter. When the tag-team bout against Zangief is televised, Sakura's rival Karin becomes incensed at Sakura's newfound glory and decides to challenge her to another battle.

Karin's anticipation for a rematch with Sakura quickly turns to disgust when Sakura decides that their next contest shouldn't be a martial arts battle, but a hot-dog eating contest. Nevertheless, Karin accepts then departs, while Sakura undertakes a training regime with some help from Kei and Shoma.

However, as the contest gets underway, it becomes apparent that Karin has something in mind beyond a sporting victory. Meanwhile, Dan recovers from his injuries and sets out again to track down Sakura.
A full blown battle royal breaks out between Karin with her servants and Sakura and her Rival Schools friends. Afterwards, Dan finally catches up with Sakura.

For over twenty years, the character Vampire Hunter D has haunted the imaginations of people around the world, its image forever etched in the mind's eye through the dazzling artwork of Yoshitaka Amano. As the original novels appear in English for the first time, American readers are clamoring for a more extensive look at this singular creation. Coffin obliges. This gorgeous retrospective embraces the full scope of Amano's work with the character: in the novels, as inspiration for the animators of the two theatrical films, rare paintings, and illustrations created for release as limited edition prints.
name: HC

volume.name: Coffin: The Art of Vampire Hunter D

description: Since Dark Horse and Digital Manga Publishing started releasing English-language editions of the Vampire Hunter D novels in 2005, hundreds of thousands of new fans have clamored for more of the enigmatic monster slayer. Following on the heels of the highly successful retrospective Coffin, Dark Horse Books is pleased to present a new collection of paintings, line-art illustrations, and photography by internationally renowned artist and Vampire Hunter D character designer Yoshitaka Amano. This collection also includes a short story, "A Village in Fog" by Vampire Hunter D creator Hideyuki Kikuchi, unavailable elsewhere.
name: Collected Art of Vampire Hunter D

volume.name: Yoshitaka Amano: The Collected Art of Vampire Hunter D
